WEBVTT

00:04.796 --> 00:07.715
[light chime music]

00:07.715 --> 00:14.722
♪ ♪

00:20.228 --> 00:21.646
- [sighs]

00:21.646 --> 00:22.689
[door clicks open]

00:24.232 --> 00:25.233
- Eleanor?

00:25.233 --> 00:27.569
Come on in.

00:27.569 --> 00:30.905
[light chiming continues]

00:30.905 --> 00:37.912
♪ ♪

00:37.912 --> 00:39.956
Hi, Eleanor.
I'm Michael.

00:39.956 --> 00:42.041
How are you today?

00:42.041 --> 00:44.377
- I'm great.
Thanks for asking.

00:44.377 --> 00:46.087
Oh, one question.

00:46.087 --> 00:47.756
Where am I?

00:47.756 --> 00:49.382
Who are you?
And what's going on?

00:49.382 --> 00:51.551
- Right, so,

00:51.551 --> 00:53.178
you, Eleanor Shellstrop,

00:53.178 --> 00:54.387
are dead.

00:54.387 --> 00:56.014
Your life on Earth has ended,

00:56.014 --> 00:58.057
and you are now
in the next phase

00:58.057 --> 01:01.060
of your existence
in the universe.

01:02.604 --> 01:04.439
- Cool.

01:04.439 --> 01:06.858
Cool.
I have some questions.

01:06.858 --> 01:08.193
- Thought you might.
[chuckles]

01:08.193 --> 01:09.194
- How did I die?

01:09.194 --> 01:10.695
I-I don't remember.

01:10.695 --> 01:11.780
- Yes, um,

01:11.780 --> 01:14.115
in cases of traumatic
or embarrassing deaths,

01:14.115 --> 01:18.787
we erase the memory to allow
for a peaceful transition.

01:18.787 --> 01:20.830
Are you sure you want to hear?

01:20.830 --> 01:24.000
All right, so you were
in a grocery store parking lot.

01:24.000 --> 01:25.960
You dropped a bottle
of something called

01:25.960 --> 01:29.130
"Lonely Gal Margarita Mix
for One."

01:29.130 --> 01:31.216
And when you bent down
to pick it up,

01:31.216 --> 01:33.802
a long column of shopping carts

01:33.802 --> 01:36.596
that were being returned to the
shopping cart collection area

01:36.596 --> 01:40.141
rolled out of control
and plowed right into you.

01:40.141 --> 01:41.434
- Oof.

01:41.434 --> 01:42.477
That's how I died?

01:42.477 --> 01:43.811
- No, sorry, there's more.

01:43.811 --> 01:45.230
You were able to grab on

01:45.230 --> 01:46.981
to the front of the column
of shopping carts,

01:46.981 --> 01:49.150
but it swept you
right out into the street

01:49.150 --> 01:50.985
where you were struck
and killed

01:50.985 --> 01:54.656
by a mobile billboard truck
advertising

01:54.656 --> 01:58.826
an erectile dysfunction pill
called "Engorge-ulate."

01:58.826 --> 02:01.120
Funnily enough,
the first EMT to arrive

02:01.120 --> 02:02.372
was an ex-boyfriend of yours--

02:02.372 --> 02:03.873
- Okay, that's--
I get it, thank you.

02:03.873 --> 02:05.124
- Oh, okay, sorry.

02:05.124 --> 02:07.293
- Um, so who was right?

02:07.293 --> 02:10.088
I mean about all of this?

02:10.088 --> 02:13.007
- Well, let's see.
Hindus are a little bit right,

02:13.007 --> 02:14.759
Muslims a little bit.

02:14.759 --> 02:17.262
Jews, Christians, Buddhists.

02:17.262 --> 02:20.640
Every religion
guessed about 5%,

02:20.640 --> 02:22.016
except for Doug Forcett.

02:22.016 --> 02:23.685
- Who--who's Doug Forcett?

02:23.685 --> 02:25.770
- Well, Doug was a stoner kid

02:25.770 --> 02:28.523
who lived in Calgary
during the 1970s.

02:28.523 --> 02:30.775
One night, he got
really high on mushrooms,

02:30.775 --> 02:33.194
and his best friend,
Randy, said,

02:33.194 --> 02:35.697
"Hey, what do you think
happens after we die?"

02:35.697 --> 02:39.450
And Doug just launched
into this long monologue

02:39.450 --> 02:42.203
where he got like 92% correct.
[chuckles]

02:42.203 --> 02:44.664
I mean, we couldn't believe
what we were hearing.

02:44.664 --> 02:46.583
That's him, actually,
right up there.

02:46.583 --> 02:48.543
He's pretty famous around here.

02:48.543 --> 02:50.044
I'm very lucky to have that.

02:50.044 --> 02:51.129
- So...
- [chuckles]

02:51.129 --> 02:52.380
- Maybe my biggest question:

02:52.380 --> 02:53.840
am I--

02:53.840 --> 02:56.301
I mean, is this...

02:57.719 --> 02:59.721
Or...

02:59.721 --> 03:01.973
- Well, it's not the

03:01.973 --> 03:05.518
heaven or hell idea
that you were raised on.

03:05.518 --> 03:07.687
But generally speaking,

03:07.687 --> 03:10.398
in the afterlife,
there's a Good Place

03:10.398 --> 03:13.651
and there's a Bad Place.

03:13.651 --> 03:15.236
You're in the Good Place.

03:15.236 --> 03:17.405
- [exhales sharply]
- You're okay, Eleanor.

03:17.405 --> 03:19.240
You're in the Good Place.

03:19.240 --> 03:20.909
- Well, that's good.

03:20.909 --> 03:22.911
- Sure is.
[laughs]

03:22.911 --> 03:25.580
Okay, let's take a walk,
shall we?

03:27.123 --> 03:29.125
- Oh, did I
have a purse?

03:29.125 --> 03:31.586
No, I'm dead, right.
Okay.

03:31.586 --> 03:34.589
[bright instrumental music]

03:34.589 --> 03:36.591
♪ ♪

03:36.591 --> 03:38.426
- So, are you...

03:38.426 --> 03:40.678
I mean, this sounds like
a crazy question,

03:40.678 --> 03:42.221
but are you God?

03:42.221 --> 03:43.681
- Oh, no, no, no, no.

03:43.681 --> 03:45.933
There are many levels
above me, Eleanor,

03:45.933 --> 03:49.228
before you get to
the Supreme Commander Zortraxx,

03:49.228 --> 03:54.067
the Merciless Frog God--
Long May He Reign.

03:54.067 --> 03:56.069
I'm kidding!
[laughing]

03:56.069 --> 03:58.404
I'm sorry!
No, no, no, no, no.

03:58.404 --> 04:01.282
It's not a giant frog.
- Oh. Whew!

04:01.282 --> 04:03.785
- No, it's just
my little joke.

04:03.785 --> 04:06.120
Seriously, though,
I'm not a god, Eleanor.

04:06.120 --> 04:07.914
I'm--I'm an architect,

04:07.914 --> 04:10.416
and I designed this
neighborhood.

04:10.416 --> 04:11.959
So this is how it works.

04:11.959 --> 04:15.129
The Good Place is divided
into distinct neighborhoods.

04:15.129 --> 04:18.800
Each one contains
exactly 322 people

04:18.800 --> 04:20.635
who have been
perfectly selected

04:20.635 --> 04:24.764
to blend together into
a blissful harmonic balance.

04:24.764 --> 04:26.975
- Do all the neighborhoods
look like this?

04:26.975 --> 04:28.476
- No, every neighborhood
is unique.

04:28.476 --> 04:30.478
Some have warm weather,
some cold.

04:30.478 --> 04:32.814
Some are cities,
some farmland.

04:32.814 --> 04:35.900
But in each one,
every blade of grass,

04:35.900 --> 04:37.276
every ladybug,

04:37.276 --> 04:39.445
every detail has been

04:39.445 --> 04:41.322
precisely
designed and calibrated

04:41.322 --> 04:42.657
for its residents.

04:42.657 --> 04:45.118
- There's a lot
of frozen yogurt places.

04:45.118 --> 04:46.577
- Yeah. [sighs]

04:46.577 --> 04:48.454
That's the one thing we put
in all the neighborhoods.

04:48.454 --> 04:50.206
People love frozen yogurt.

04:50.206 --> 04:52.333
I don't know what to tell you.

04:52.333 --> 04:54.961
You're gonna have a million
more questions, I know.

04:54.961 --> 04:56.337
For right now,

04:56.337 --> 04:57.505
better grab a seat.

04:57.505 --> 05:00.508
Movie's about to begin.

05:00.508 --> 05:03.511
[indistinct chatter]

05:05.179 --> 05:06.180
Ah.
[chuckles]

05:06.180 --> 05:07.682
Hello, everyone.

05:07.682 --> 05:12.270
And welcome to your first day
in the afterlife.

05:12.270 --> 05:15.690
You were all,
simply put, good people.

05:15.690 --> 05:18.026
But how do we know
that you were good?

05:18.026 --> 05:20.361
How are we sure?

05:20.361 --> 05:22.030
During your time on Earth,

05:22.030 --> 05:23.698
every one of your actions

05:23.698 --> 05:26.868
had a positive
or a negative value,

05:26.868 --> 05:29.203
depending
on how much good or bad

05:29.203 --> 05:31.831
that action
put into the universe.

05:31.831 --> 05:34.083
Every sandwich you ate,

05:34.083 --> 05:35.960
every time
you bought a magazine,

05:35.960 --> 05:38.546
every single thing you did

05:38.546 --> 05:41.632
had an effect
that rippled out over time

05:41.632 --> 05:45.219
and ultimately created
some amount of good or bad.

05:45.219 --> 05:47.305
You know how some people
pull into the breakdown lane

05:47.305 --> 05:48.347
when there's traffic?

05:48.347 --> 05:49.557
And they think to themselves,

05:49.557 --> 05:52.393
"Ah, who cares?
No one's watching."

05:52.393 --> 05:53.895
We were watching.

05:53.895 --> 05:54.979
Surprise.

05:54.979 --> 05:56.314
[laughter]

05:56.314 --> 05:59.067
Anyway, when your time
on Earth has ended,

05:59.067 --> 06:02.320
we calculate
the total value of your life

06:02.320 --> 06:05.490
using our perfectly accurate
measuring system.

06:05.490 --> 06:08.493
Only the people
with the very highest scores,

06:08.493 --> 06:09.911
the true cream of the crop,

06:09.911 --> 06:12.205
get to come here,
to the Good Place.

06:12.205 --> 06:14.791
What happens to everyone else,
you ask?

06:14.791 --> 06:16.250
Don't worry about it.

06:16.250 --> 06:18.836
The point is, you are here
because you lived

06:18.836 --> 06:20.588
one of the very best lives

06:20.588 --> 06:21.923
that could be lived.

06:21.923 --> 06:24.258
And you won't be alone.

06:24.258 --> 06:26.928
Your true soul mate
is here too.

06:26.928 --> 06:28.596
[crowd gasps and murmurs]
That's right.

06:28.596 --> 06:29.931
Soul mates are real.

06:29.931 --> 06:32.517
One of the other people
in your neighborhood

06:32.517 --> 06:34.602
is your actual soul mate,

06:34.602 --> 06:38.439
and you will spend
eternity together.

06:38.439 --> 06:41.109
So welcome
to eternal happiness.

06:41.109 --> 06:43.277
Welcome to the Good Place.

06:43.277 --> 06:44.570
Sponsored by:

06:44.570 --> 06:46.781
otters holding hands
while they sleep.

06:46.781 --> 06:48.449
You know the way you feel
when you see

06:48.449 --> 06:51.285
a picture of two otters
holding hands?

06:51.285 --> 06:54.622
That's how you're gonna feel
every day.

06:54.622 --> 06:57.250
[applause]

06:57.250 --> 07:00.127
- So who is in the Bad Place,
that would shock me?

07:00.127 --> 07:02.463
- Uh, well, Mozart,

07:02.463 --> 07:04.131
Picasso, Elvis--

07:04.131 --> 07:06.133
basically every artist ever,

07:06.133 --> 07:08.302
uh, every U. S. president
except Lincoln.

07:08.302 --> 07:09.720
- That sounds about right.

07:09.720 --> 07:11.222
- Walt Disney.
- Really!

07:11.222 --> 07:14.308
- Oh, yeah, yeah.
They went to town on Disney.

07:14.308 --> 07:18.396
He has to spend eternity
in a broken-down boat

07:18.396 --> 07:22.233
on the Small World ride
with eight very tired children,

07:22.233 --> 07:24.777
and they made it so he
really has to pee! [laughs]

07:24.777 --> 07:26.404
What about
Florence Nightingale?

07:26.404 --> 07:28.322
- That was close,
but, no, she didn't make it.

07:28.322 --> 07:30.992
- Wow, all those
amazing people down there--

07:30.992 --> 07:33.160
it just seems
so hard to believe.

07:33.160 --> 07:36.539
- Again, it's an incredibly
selective system.

07:36.539 --> 07:38.541
Most people
don't make it here.

07:38.541 --> 07:43.087
But you, a lawyer who got
innocent people off death row,

07:43.087 --> 07:45.840
you're special, Eleanor.

07:45.840 --> 07:47.967
And by the way,

07:47.967 --> 07:50.094
welcome to your new home.

07:50.094 --> 07:52.096
Oh, it's perfect,
isn't it?

07:52.096 --> 07:53.764
You see,
in the Good Place,

07:53.764 --> 07:55.683
every person
gets to live in a home

07:55.683 --> 07:59.437
that perfectly matches
his or her true essence.

07:59.437 --> 08:00.688
- Cool.

08:00.688 --> 08:03.774
So I guess that's why
my house, for example,

08:03.774 --> 08:05.776
is this adorable little cottage,

08:05.776 --> 08:09.322
whereas other people might
have homes that are bigger,

08:09.322 --> 08:10.531
like that one.

08:10.531 --> 08:12.325
- Exactly.

08:12.325 --> 08:14.535
Oh, I'm so happy you get it.

08:14.535 --> 08:16.871
As you can see,
the interior has been

08:16.871 --> 08:18.831
decorated just as you like it,

08:18.831 --> 08:21.876
in the Icelandic
primitive style.

08:21.876 --> 08:24.629
Oh, oh, and, uh,
of course,

08:24.629 --> 08:27.465
you love clowns, so...

08:27.465 --> 08:29.467
- I do love clowns.

08:29.467 --> 08:31.052
- Now, let me show you
the, uh--

08:31.052 --> 08:33.012
the video system here.

08:33.012 --> 08:34.722
[shimmering tone]

08:34.722 --> 08:37.058
You can review everything
that happened in your life

08:37.058 --> 08:40.061
from your point of view.

08:40.061 --> 08:41.395
There we go.

08:41.395 --> 08:44.065
This is your Human Rights
mission to the Ukraine.

08:44.065 --> 08:46.359
I mean, you got
a ton of points for that one.

08:46.359 --> 08:48.736
It really put you
over the top.

08:48.736 --> 08:50.321
Oh.

08:50.321 --> 08:52.073
Chidi, come on in.

08:52.073 --> 08:54.033
- Eleanor?

08:54.033 --> 08:57.203
I-I'm Chidi Anagonye,

08:57.203 --> 09:00.081
and you are
my soul mate.

09:01.624 --> 09:04.210
- Cool, bring it in, man.

09:04.210 --> 09:05.336
- Now, excuse me.

09:05.336 --> 09:07.171
I have other people
to attend to.

09:07.171 --> 09:09.423
- So where you from,
Chidi?

09:09.423 --> 09:11.926
- Well, I was born
in Nigeria,

09:11.926 --> 09:13.094
raised in Senegal,

09:13.094 --> 09:15.263
but my work took me
all over the place--

09:15.263 --> 09:18.099
Australia, Hong Kong, Paris.

09:18.099 --> 09:19.600
What about you?

09:19.600 --> 09:22.019
- Uh, well, I--
I was born in Phoenix.

09:22.019 --> 09:23.521
- Mm-hmm.
- Arizona.

09:23.521 --> 09:26.357
And then I went to school
in Tempe, Arizona.

09:26.357 --> 09:30.695
And then I moved back
to Phoenix, Arizona.

09:31.779 --> 09:33.447
Your English is amazing.

09:33.447 --> 09:35.116
- Oh!

09:35.116 --> 09:37.243
I'm actually speaking French.

09:37.243 --> 09:39.078
This place just translates
whatever you say

09:39.078 --> 09:41.289
into a language
the other person can understand.

09:41.289 --> 09:43.165
So it's incredible.
- Whoa.

09:43.165 --> 09:45.459
- And now I want to say this.

09:45.459 --> 09:46.711
- Mm-kay.

09:46.711 --> 09:47.878
- Eleanor.

09:47.878 --> 09:50.131
I have spent
my entire life

09:50.131 --> 09:53.384
in pursuit of fundamental truths
about the universe.

09:53.384 --> 09:55.636
And now we can
actually learn about them

09:55.636 --> 09:59.390
together as soul mates.

09:59.390 --> 10:02.601
It's overwhelming.

10:02.601 --> 10:03.978
- Chidi.

10:03.978 --> 10:06.814
You'll stand by my side
no matter what, right?

10:06.814 --> 10:08.107
- Of course I will.

10:08.107 --> 10:10.651
- Promise me.
Say, "I promise

10:10.651 --> 10:13.988
I will never betray you
for any reason."

10:13.988 --> 10:15.448
- Eleanor, I swear

10:15.448 --> 10:19.327
that I will never say
or do anything

10:19.327 --> 10:21.412
to cause you any harm.

10:21.412 --> 10:22.872
- Good.

10:22.872 --> 10:24.290
Because those
aren't my memories.

10:24.290 --> 10:26.500
I wasn't a lawyer.
I never went to the Ukraine.

10:26.500 --> 10:28.794
I hate clowns.

10:28.794 --> 10:31.505
There's been a big mistake.

10:31.505 --> 10:33.966
I'm not supposed to be here.

10:37.511 --> 10:38.637
- Wait, what?

10:43.768 --> 10:44.268
[light instrumental music]

10:45.269 --> 10:46.687
[croaking]

10:46.687 --> 10:48.606
♪ ♪

10:48.606 --> 10:51.192
[children chattering,
meowing]

10:51.192 --> 10:52.651
- Are you sure this isn't you?

10:52.651 --> 10:54.362
- Yeah, man,
I'm pretty sure

10:54.362 --> 10:56.197
I wasn't a death row lawyer

10:56.197 --> 10:58.032
who collected clown paintings

10:58.032 --> 10:59.825
and rescued orphans.

10:59.825 --> 11:02.036
They got my name right,
but nothing else.

11:02.036 --> 11:05.581
I mean, somebody
royally forked up.

11:05.581 --> 11:08.084
Somebody forked up.

11:08.084 --> 11:09.377
Why can't I say "fork"?

11:09.377 --> 11:11.212
- If you're trying to curse,
you can't here.

11:11.212 --> 11:12.797
I guess a lot of people
in this neighborhood

11:12.797 --> 11:14.340
don't like it,
so it's prohibited.

11:14.340 --> 11:15.549
- That's bullshirt.

11:15.549 --> 11:17.676
- So, uh, if you're
not this person,

11:17.676 --> 11:19.387
then who are you?

11:19.387 --> 11:20.554
What did you do
for a living?

11:20.554 --> 11:23.849
- I was... in...

11:23.849 --> 11:24.892
sales.

11:24.892 --> 11:26.560
- So we sell
two products here,

11:26.560 --> 11:28.062
NasaPRO and
NasaPRO Silver.

11:28.062 --> 11:29.313
We aim this at seniors.

11:29.313 --> 11:31.565
Now, you can't legally
call it medicine

11:31.565 --> 11:34.819
because it doesn't
technically... work

11:34.819 --> 11:37.738
and it is technically...
chalk,

11:37.738 --> 11:38.906
so what you're gonna
want to do--

11:38.906 --> 11:40.074
- You need me
to lie to old people

11:40.074 --> 11:41.909
and scare them
into buying fake medicine.

11:41.909 --> 11:44.245
I get it, man.
Which one's my desk?

11:44.245 --> 11:46.539
- So your job

11:46.539 --> 11:48.791
was to defraud the elderly?

11:48.791 --> 11:51.585
Sorry--
the sick and elderly?

11:51.585 --> 11:52.920
- But I was very good at it.

11:52.920 --> 11:55.256
I was the top salesperson
five years running.

11:55.256 --> 11:56.549
- Okay, but that's worse.

11:56.549 --> 11:58.926
I mean, you--you do get
how that's worse,

11:58.926 --> 12:00.678
right?
- Mm.

12:00.678 --> 12:01.887
[indistinct chatter]

12:01.887 --> 12:03.681
You know, maybe...

12:03.681 --> 12:04.932
it's a test.

12:04.932 --> 12:07.601
Maybe if you go to Michael
and you tell him the truth,

12:07.601 --> 12:10.187
you'll pass the test
and you'll get to stay.

12:10.187 --> 12:11.272
- No way.

12:11.272 --> 12:12.690
I can't risk going
to the Bad Place.

12:12.690 --> 12:14.608
- Okay, well, maybe
it's not actually, like,

12:14.608 --> 12:15.776
all that bad.

12:15.776 --> 12:17.778
Let's just get
some information first.

12:17.778 --> 12:19.447
We'll ask Janet.
Hey, Janet?

12:19.447 --> 12:20.448
- Hi there.
- Gah!

12:20.448 --> 12:21.449
- How can I help you?

12:21.449 --> 12:23.117
- What the fork?
Who are you?

12:23.117 --> 12:24.452
- I'm Janet.

12:24.452 --> 12:26.787
I'm the informational assistant
here in the Good Place.

12:26.787 --> 12:29.165
- She's like this
walking database.

12:29.165 --> 12:31.000
You can ask her about

12:31.000 --> 12:33.210
the creation of the universe
or history--

12:33.210 --> 12:34.962
- Oh, there was
a guy who lived

12:34.962 --> 12:37.381
in Avondale, Arizona,
around 2002.

12:37.381 --> 12:39.300
His name was Kevin Paltonic.

12:39.300 --> 12:41.093
Is he gay?
- No.

12:41.093 --> 12:43.304
- Really?
Huh.

12:43.304 --> 12:45.389
I guess he just didn't wanna
have sex with me.

12:45.389 --> 12:46.807
- That's correct.
- Well, that's fine.

12:46.807 --> 12:48.642
I wasn't that into him anyway.
- Yes, you were.

12:48.642 --> 12:49.643
- Okay, Janet,

12:49.643 --> 12:50.978
I have a question.
- Okay.

12:50.978 --> 12:53.814
- What is the Bad Place like?

12:53.814 --> 12:55.983
- Oh, sorry,
that is the one topic

12:55.983 --> 12:57.776
I'm not allowed
to tell you about.

12:57.776 --> 13:00.446
I can only play you
a brief audio clip

13:00.446 --> 13:02.781
of what is happening there
right now.

13:02.781 --> 13:04.158
- Okay.

13:04.158 --> 13:06.243
[people yelling and screaming,
mechanical buzzing]

13:06.243 --> 13:08.996
- The bear has two mouths!
[people screaming]

13:08.996 --> 13:10.498
[sound cuts off]

13:10.498 --> 13:13.167
- Well, it doesn't sound
awesome.

13:13.167 --> 13:15.294
[scoffs]

13:15.294 --> 13:18.005
Does everyone have
a huge house except me?

13:18.005 --> 13:19.465
All right, we need a plan.

13:19.465 --> 13:20.966
I say we just lie low

13:20.966 --> 13:22.259
and hope that
they don't notice me.

13:22.259 --> 13:24.011
- I'm sorry,
I don't think I can help you.

13:24.011 --> 13:25.679
I just don't like
being dishonest,

13:25.679 --> 13:28.974
and I can't advise you
to be dishonest either.

13:28.974 --> 13:31.477
- Come on, I'm just asking
you to fudge a little bit.

13:31.477 --> 13:33.854
You must've told a few
white lies in your life.

13:33.854 --> 13:35.272
I mean, what was your job?

13:35.272 --> 13:38.275
- I was a professor of ethics
and moral philosophy.

13:38.275 --> 13:40.861
- Motherforker!

13:40.861 --> 13:42.696
- I'm getting a stomachache.

13:42.696 --> 13:44.448
I'm in a perfect utopia,

13:44.448 --> 13:45.991
and I'm--I have a stomachache.

13:45.991 --> 13:47.326
This is awful.

13:47.326 --> 13:49.370
I-I, uh--I think I have
to tell Michael about this.

13:49.370 --> 13:51.080
- Tell Michael about what?

13:51.080 --> 13:52.915
- Michael?
Hi.

13:52.915 --> 13:54.541
What have you
been up to?

13:54.541 --> 13:57.044
- Oh, you know, just
settling everyone in

13:57.044 --> 13:58.879
to eternal paradise.

13:58.879 --> 14:00.172
- Sure, sure.

14:00.172 --> 14:01.966
- Eleanor, Chidi,
I would like you to meet

14:01.966 --> 14:03.717
Tahani and Jianyu.

14:03.717 --> 14:05.219
They are soul mates

14:05.219 --> 14:07.054
and your next-door
neighbors.

14:07.054 --> 14:08.222
- Hello.

14:08.222 --> 14:11.058
Can I just say
I love your house?

14:11.058 --> 14:14.395
It's just so
tiny and cute.

14:14.395 --> 14:15.980
It's like a little child's
plaything.

14:15.980 --> 14:18.524
It's a bit like one of
those Tinkertoy houses,

14:18.524 --> 14:20.567
isn't it,
like for a family of mice

14:20.567 --> 14:22.820
or for a very
fancy little dog.

14:22.820 --> 14:26.240
I love it.
It's just so sweet and teensy.

14:26.240 --> 14:28.242
Just like you.

14:28.242 --> 14:29.368
Boop!
- Oh.

14:29.368 --> 14:30.911
- Oh!
- You booped me.

14:30.911 --> 14:31.912
Ha-ha.

14:31.912 --> 14:33.622
- I did.
- That's fun.

14:33.622 --> 14:37.042
- Oh, the thought
of you four amazing people

14:37.042 --> 14:40.170
living next to each other
for eternity just...

14:40.170 --> 14:41.505
it brings joy to my heart.

14:41.505 --> 14:43.590
Oh! I almost forgot.

14:43.590 --> 14:45.426
Tahani and Jianyu
are having a little

14:45.426 --> 14:47.344
welcome party tonight,
and they've invited

14:47.344 --> 14:49.096
the entire neighborhood.

14:49.096 --> 14:50.597
- Is that because
your house is so big

14:50.597 --> 14:52.266
it can fit everybody?

14:52.266 --> 14:53.517
- Exactly. Yes!

14:53.517 --> 14:56.020
But also because
I simply adore entertaining.

14:56.020 --> 14:58.105
I just adore it.

14:58.105 --> 15:00.941
Don't I just adore it,
Jianyu?

15:00.941 --> 15:02.526
Oh, um, yes, by the way,

15:02.526 --> 15:05.612
Jianyu here is a Buddhist monk,
you see?

15:05.612 --> 15:08.115
And he obeys
a strict code of silence.

15:08.115 --> 15:10.617
So when you see him
smiling and nodding,

15:10.617 --> 15:14.121
that's actually his way of
jumping up and down with glee.

15:14.121 --> 15:17.416
Isn't that right, darling?

15:17.416 --> 15:18.709
So we'll see you tonight?

15:18.709 --> 15:20.419
- Great.
- Yes.

15:20.419 --> 15:22.296
♪ ♪

15:22.296 --> 15:24.048
- This is a sweet dress,
right?

15:24.048 --> 15:25.466
- Yeah.
- I had Janet fetch it for me.

15:25.466 --> 15:27.968
Instant, on-demand.
Everything free.

15:27.968 --> 15:29.970
[laughing]
This place is the best!

15:29.970 --> 15:32.056
[classical music plays]
[guests chatter]

15:32.056 --> 15:34.350
[Chidi chuckles]
- No way.

15:35.642 --> 15:37.811
My entire house
could fit in this room.

15:37.811 --> 15:39.563
- Okay, uh...

15:39.563 --> 15:40.981
help me out here.

15:40.981 --> 15:42.483
Tell me one good thing

15:42.483 --> 15:44.318
that you did on Earth,

15:44.318 --> 15:47.488
just one truly kind
and decent act

15:47.488 --> 15:50.407
so that I can feel better
about helping you out.

15:52.993 --> 15:54.328
Let's forget about good.

15:54.328 --> 15:56.872
Um, just tell me something
neutral about yourself.

15:56.872 --> 15:58.665
Like, tell me about
the day before you died.

15:58.665 --> 16:01.627
What do you remember?

16:01.627 --> 16:02.795
- Hi there.

16:02.795 --> 16:04.254
Do you have a second
to talk about the environment?

16:04.254 --> 16:07.007
- Do you have a second
to eat my farts?

16:07.007 --> 16:08.008
- You missed.

16:08.008 --> 16:09.301
- [scoffs]
Pick it up

16:09.301 --> 16:10.844
if you're so horny
for the environment.

16:10.844 --> 16:13.263
I don't remember
anything specific.

16:13.263 --> 16:14.515
- Oh.
- Look.

16:14.515 --> 16:15.849
I might not
have been a saint,

16:15.849 --> 16:17.976
but it's not like
I killed anybody.

16:17.976 --> 16:19.353
I wasn't an arsonist.

16:19.353 --> 16:21.522
I never found a wallet
outside of an IHOP and

16:21.522 --> 16:23.816
thought about returning it but
saw the owner lived out of state

16:23.816 --> 16:25.359
so just took the cash
and dropped the wallet

16:25.359 --> 16:27.111
back on the ground.

16:27.111 --> 16:28.445
- Okay, that's really specific,

16:28.445 --> 16:30.614
and that makes me think that
you definitely did do that.

16:30.614 --> 16:32.449
- All I'm saying is

16:32.449 --> 16:34.827
these people might be "good,"

16:34.827 --> 16:38.330
but are they really
that much better than me?

16:38.330 --> 16:40.749
- Well, I spent half my life
in North Korea

16:40.749 --> 16:42.209
fighting for women's rights

16:42.209 --> 16:43.710
and the other half
in Saudi Arabia

16:43.710 --> 16:45.170
fighting for gay rights.

16:45.170 --> 16:47.548
- So we said, "If the U. N.
won't remove those land mines,

16:47.548 --> 16:48.715
we will."

16:48.715 --> 16:51.510
And we dug up over a thousand
unexploded land mines

16:51.510 --> 16:53.303
from the area
surrounding the orphanage.

16:53.303 --> 16:54.721
- Well, then he said,

16:54.721 --> 16:56.640
"You can't give me both
your kidneys; you'll die."

16:56.640 --> 16:58.559
And I said,
"But you will live.

16:58.559 --> 17:00.519
"And I know we just met
on this bus ten minutes ago,

17:00.519 --> 17:01.520
but you seem nice."

17:01.520 --> 17:02.563
- [groans]
Oh, forget it.

17:02.563 --> 17:04.231
Heading to the bar!

17:09.486 --> 17:10.529
Hey, Janet?
- Hi!

17:10.529 --> 17:11.738
How can I help?

17:11.738 --> 17:13.157
- Um...

17:13.157 --> 17:15.576
I've had eight
glasses of wine,

17:15.576 --> 17:17.536
and I don't feel
anything.

17:17.536 --> 17:19.955
Can we not get drunk
here?

17:19.955 --> 17:23.417
It's suddenly very important
that I get drunk.

17:23.417 --> 17:26.753
- Our default setting
is that alcohol has no effect.

17:26.753 --> 17:29.256
If you want it to affect you,
all you have to do

17:29.256 --> 17:32.050
is think to yourself--
- Got it. On it.

17:35.596 --> 17:37.222
Mmm!

17:37.222 --> 17:40.017
Mmm...

17:40.017 --> 17:41.101
[glass clinking]

17:41.101 --> 17:43.437
[polite applause]

17:43.437 --> 17:47.107
- Thank you, thank you.

17:47.107 --> 17:50.444
I promise I won't
take up too much time here.

17:50.444 --> 17:54.281
As Shakespeare once said,
"Brevity is the soul of wit."

17:54.281 --> 17:56.408
Although, he's actually...
wrrr!

17:56.408 --> 17:59.620
So... ha!
We can ignore that advice.

17:59.620 --> 18:03.832
You all know that I am the
architect of this neighborhood.

18:03.832 --> 18:05.751
But what you don't know is...

18:05.751 --> 18:08.796
Golly, I'm not supposed
to tell you this, but, um,

18:08.796 --> 18:10.631
oh, what the heck?

18:10.631 --> 18:13.133
This is actually
the very first neighborhood

18:13.133 --> 18:14.635
that I have ever designed.

18:14.635 --> 18:18.222
I have been an apprentice
for over 200 years,

18:18.222 --> 18:20.307
and my boss
has finally given me

18:20.307 --> 18:22.601
my first solo project.

18:22.601 --> 18:24.478
[murmurs and applause]
Yes!

18:24.478 --> 18:26.480
[laughs]

18:26.480 --> 18:28.899
- Ah, gah-gah--gah-gah-gah.
Hold on there, ace.

18:28.899 --> 18:30.484
Let me get more
of them shrampies.

18:30.484 --> 18:31.985
- Okay, easy.
- What?

18:31.985 --> 18:33.320
They're for everybody,
right?

18:33.320 --> 18:34.780
- Yes, exactly.

18:34.780 --> 18:37.616
- And you deserve
a perfect world

18:37.616 --> 18:41.328
because every single one of you

18:41.328 --> 18:43.372
is a good person.

18:43.372 --> 18:45.707
That's it for me.
Back to you, Tahani.

18:45.707 --> 18:48.836
- Bravo, Michael, bravo!
- Thank you.

18:48.836 --> 18:51.004
- Um, and I would just like
to quickly say

18:51.004 --> 18:53.340
if any of you would like
to play tennis tonight,

18:53.340 --> 18:56.593
we have 36 regulation
grass tennis courts.

18:56.593 --> 18:58.929
Such fun. Cheers.
[laughs]

18:58.929 --> 19:00.097
[applause]

19:00.097 --> 19:03.100
- Tahani--
what a condescending bench.

19:03.100 --> 19:04.601
- Okay, okay, okay, okay.
- Am I right?

19:04.601 --> 19:06.520
Why does she still have
that British accent, right?

19:06.520 --> 19:08.105
No one else here
has an accent.

19:08.105 --> 19:09.690
She's choosing
to have that accent.

19:09.690 --> 19:10.691
- Shh-shh-shh-shh.

19:10.691 --> 19:12.860
- [stodgily] "Oh, hello.

19:12.860 --> 19:14.486
"I am just a big, beautiful,

19:14.486 --> 19:16.947
utterly perfect
cartoon giraffe."

19:16.947 --> 19:18.365
- Oh, okay. Okay.
- [laughing mockingly]

19:18.365 --> 19:20.784
- I think it's time
to go home.

19:20.784 --> 19:23.120
- Wait, wait, wait.
I just have to go upstairs

19:23.120 --> 19:25.372
real quick and steal
a bunch of gold stuff.

19:25.372 --> 19:28.208
- Okay, don't do that.

19:28.208 --> 19:30.252
Don't do--no, Eleanor,
Eleanor, Eleanor.

19:34.756 --> 19:37.885
- Hello, creepy house
that I hate.

19:37.885 --> 19:41.054
Hello, one million clowns.

19:41.054 --> 19:44.057
Why aren't there
stairs here?

19:44.057 --> 19:45.559
♪ ♪

19:45.559 --> 19:46.810
[groans]

19:46.810 --> 19:49.730
What kind of weirdo house
is this?

19:49.730 --> 19:52.065
Ooh.

19:52.065 --> 19:55.068
- Did you fill your bra
with shrimp?

19:55.068 --> 19:56.236
- No.

19:56.236 --> 19:57.404
[hiccups]

19:57.404 --> 19:58.405
Yes.

19:58.405 --> 20:00.407
Whatever,
it's freakin' heaven.

20:00.407 --> 20:03.327
I'm sure they have
plenty of shellfish.

20:03.327 --> 20:05.537
That Tahani is
a real butthead, huh?

20:05.537 --> 20:07.122
[gasps]
Hey!

20:07.122 --> 20:09.416
At least I can still say
"butthead."

20:09.416 --> 20:11.919
[groans]
She is a butthead.

20:11.919 --> 20:15.589
- Found some pajamas.

20:15.589 --> 20:18.050
- Chidi--
Chidi, Chidi?

20:18.050 --> 20:22.262
I'm sorry that you had
to deal with this...

20:22.262 --> 20:23.430
- It's okay.

20:23.430 --> 20:24.932
- It's not, though.

20:24.932 --> 20:25.933
[sighs]

20:25.933 --> 20:28.769
Do you think anybody
cared that I died?

20:28.769 --> 20:30.187
Maybe someone did.

20:30.187 --> 20:31.772
I don't know.

20:31.772 --> 20:33.273
I was an only child.

20:33.273 --> 20:35.567
My parents were divorced
when I was a kid.

20:35.567 --> 20:37.444
They were both crummy people,

20:37.444 --> 20:38.612
so they're probably...

20:38.612 --> 20:39.863
pffff...

20:39.863 --> 20:41.782
in the Bad Place.

20:41.782 --> 20:45.118
Maybe they're being used
to torture each other.

20:45.118 --> 20:46.286
It would work.

20:46.286 --> 20:47.621
- [chuckles]

20:47.621 --> 20:51.166
- I bet way more people
cared that you died.

20:51.166 --> 20:52.960
'Cause you're a nice person.

20:52.960 --> 20:54.461
[clears throat]

20:54.461 --> 20:57.381
You're a nice person,
Chidi...

20:57.381 --> 21:00.384
Anaconda.

21:00.384 --> 21:01.385
- Anagonye.

21:01.385 --> 21:02.970
- Aganocomonga.

21:02.970 --> 21:04.304
- Anagonye.

21:04.304 --> 21:06.139
- Ags--say it again.
- Anagonye.

21:06.139 --> 21:07.474
- No, say what you said before.

21:07.474 --> 21:08.976
- I did.
It's Anagonye.

21:08.976 --> 21:10.060
- You just changed it.

21:10.060 --> 21:11.645
- I didn't change it;
it's my name.

21:11.645 --> 21:13.480
- Argrugande.
Ariana Grande.

21:13.480 --> 21:14.982
[gasps]
That's a person.

21:14.982 --> 21:16.984
I did it!

21:16.984 --> 21:19.152
Good night.

21:20.153 --> 21:21.154
- Good night.

21:22.823 --> 21:23.824
[button clicks]

21:23.824 --> 21:26.785
[playful music]

21:26.785 --> 21:27.786
[people cheer]

21:27.786 --> 21:29.287
[playful musical flourish]

21:29.287 --> 21:31.039
Well, that's terrifying.

21:31.039 --> 21:32.624
- [snoring]

21:32.624 --> 21:34.418
[snorts]

21:34.418 --> 21:37.838
[birds chirping]

21:41.675 --> 21:45.846
- 30 glasses of wine,
and no hangover.

21:45.846 --> 21:46.972
[laughs]

21:46.972 --> 21:49.016
This place rules!

21:49.016 --> 21:52.102
[thunder crashes]

21:52.102 --> 21:53.687
[birds cawing]

21:53.687 --> 21:55.188
[pop music]

21:55.188 --> 21:58.358
- ♪ I'm stronger
than I've been before ♪

21:58.358 --> 22:00.694
♪ This is the part ♪

22:00.694 --> 22:03.030
♪ When I break free ♪

22:03.030 --> 22:05.449
♪ 'Cause I can't resist it
no more ♪

22:05.449 --> 22:07.534
- Oh, fork.

22:07.534 --> 22:10.037
- ♪ The part when I say
I don't want ya ♪

22:10.037 --> 22:13.165
♪ I'm stronger
than I've been before ♪

22:13.165 --> 22:15.333
♪ This is the part ♪

22:15.333 --> 22:17.878
♪ When I break free ♪

22:17.878 --> 22:20.172
♪ 'Cause I can't resist it
no more ♪

22:20.172 --> 22:21.298
- Michael.
- Mm?

22:21.298 --> 22:23.383
- Is that giant,
terrifying ladybug

22:23.383 --> 22:24.551
supposed to be there?

22:24.551 --> 22:26.386
- Ah, well,
great question, Tahani.

22:26.386 --> 22:28.680
No. No, it's not.

22:28.680 --> 22:30.724
I have no idea why
any of this is happening

22:30.724 --> 22:32.059
or how to control it.

22:32.059 --> 22:34.144
- Should we run away then?

22:34.144 --> 22:35.353
- Yes.

22:35.353 --> 22:36.563
- ♪ It was lethal ♪

22:36.563 --> 22:37.689
- Righto.

22:37.689 --> 22:39.191
- ♪ It was fatal ♪

22:39.191 --> 22:42.402
♪ In my dreams,
it just felt so right ♪

22:42.402 --> 22:49.326
♪ But I woke up every time ♪

22:49.326 --> 22:50.911
♪ Ooh, baby ♪

22:50.911 --> 22:52.913
♪ This is the part ♪

22:52.913 --> 22:55.457
♪ When I say I don't want ya ♪

22:55.457 --> 22:56.625
♪ I'm stronger
than I've been before ♪

22:56.625 --> 22:58.043
- Chidi, Chidi!

22:58.043 --> 22:59.503
What's going on?

22:59.503 --> 23:01.213
Why are there
giant animals everywhere?

23:01.213 --> 23:03.924
Do you hear
Ariana Grande playing?

23:03.924 --> 23:07.427
Why is everyone
wearing blue and yellow?

23:07.427 --> 23:09.346
- You're not.

23:09.346 --> 23:11.264
You're--you're the only one
who's not.

23:11.264 --> 23:15.268
Eleanor, this is all happening
because of you.

23:15.268 --> 23:17.062
- Ah, fork me.

23:22.275 --> 23:25.195
- Okay, okay. We don't know
this is because of me.

23:25.195 --> 23:28.115
- Eleanor, this place is
a perfectly made Swiss watch,

23:28.115 --> 23:29.950
and you are a wrench
in the gears.

23:29.950 --> 23:31.284
Actually, you're a hammer,

23:31.284 --> 23:33.120
just smashing the gears
into dust.

23:33.120 --> 23:34.412
- Oh, hang on.

23:34.412 --> 23:36.331
Not everybody here
is perfect, okay?

23:36.331 --> 23:37.916
Tahani
is totally condescending.

23:37.916 --> 23:39.960
And there are a couple of,

23:39.960 --> 23:41.711
you know, chunksters.

23:41.711 --> 23:43.130
- Oh, come on!

23:43.130 --> 23:44.923
- No judgment.
I'm just saying

23:44.923 --> 23:46.967
I'm not the only one
with flaws.

23:46.967 --> 23:49.553
So how can we be sure
this is my fault?

23:49.553 --> 23:50.804
- You hogged all the shrimp,

23:50.804 --> 23:52.806
and now there are shrimp
flying around.

23:52.806 --> 23:54.766
You called Tahani a giraffe,

23:54.766 --> 23:56.309
and now there are
giraffes everywhere.

23:56.309 --> 23:57.727
- Okay, fine, turns out
there are many ways

23:57.727 --> 23:58.812
to know that it was me.

23:58.812 --> 23:59.980
- Let's just face it,
Eleanor,

23:59.980 --> 24:01.565
you don't belong here.

24:03.400 --> 24:05.944
- Well, then this system sucks.

24:05.944 --> 24:08.488
What, one in a million
gets to live in paradise

24:08.488 --> 24:10.782
and everyone else
is tortured for eternity?

24:10.782 --> 24:11.992
Come on.

24:11.992 --> 24:13.994
I mean, I wasn't
freaking Gandhi,

24:13.994 --> 24:15.829
but I was okay.

24:15.829 --> 24:19.040
I was a medium person.

24:19.040 --> 24:22.002
I should get to spend eternity
in a medium place!

24:22.002 --> 24:23.461
Like Cincinnati.

24:23.461 --> 24:25.672
Everyone who wasn't perfect
but wasn't terrible

24:25.672 --> 24:28.008
should get to spend eternity
in Cincinnati.

24:28.008 --> 24:30.135
- Look, apparently
it doesn't work that way.

24:30.135 --> 24:31.803
I'm sorry, Eleanor,

24:31.803 --> 24:34.598
but there's nothing
anyone can do.

24:36.016 --> 24:38.018
- Unless...

24:38.018 --> 24:39.853
there is something
we can do.

24:39.853 --> 24:42.689
Unless you could teach me.

24:42.689 --> 24:44.107
- Teach you what?

24:44.107 --> 24:45.442
- How to be good.

24:45.442 --> 24:46.985
That was your job, right?

24:46.985 --> 24:48.862
A professor of ethics?

24:48.862 --> 24:51.364
No one knew I was a problem
when I arrived.

24:51.364 --> 24:52.782
Things only started
getting crazy

24:52.782 --> 24:55.118
